 SEGUN AYINDE, ABEOKUTA Police in Ogun State have arrested a 35-year- old man Ayegunle Adekunle for allegedly having an unlawful carnal knowledge of a 3-year-old girl. The suspect who is a co-tenant to the girl’s parents at No 29, Ore Meji Street, Oriokuta, Ota, was said to have lured the girl (name withheld) into his room where he had sex with her. The Police Public Relations Officer, Abimbola Oyeyemi said that the suspect was later arrested following a report by the victim’s mother who reported the case at Onipanu Division Headquarters in Ota, that she saw a blood stain in the paints of her daughter. Oyeyemi said that the blood stain raised the mother’s suspicion which prompted her to remove the paint of her daughter and discovered that she was bleeding from her private part. He said that the minor, upon enquiry opened up to her mother how Adekunle lured her into his room and forcefully had a carnal knowledge of her. According to him, the DPO Onipanu division, SP Sangobiyi Johnson, upon the complaint, detailed his detectives to the scene where the suspect was promptly arrested. The Police Spokesperson said that the suspect confessed to the commission of the crime blaming it on the devil’s handiwork. The victim has been taken to hospital for medical attention and report. Meanwhile, the Commissioner of Police CP Ahmed Iliyasu has directed that the case be transferred to Anti-Human Trafficking and Child Labour Unit of the State Criminal Investigation and Intelligence Department for further investigation and prosecution. 